version_description: Better play all in power chords on the electric guitar, so that the minor C# becomes an C#5, B to B5, A# to A#5... you got it. But for acoustic this should work.
On an electric guitar I'd recommend to use powerchords throughout the entire song.
Original Key is Cm, with Capo 1. Fret Key is Bm.
